-- EXCLUSIVE-Peru central bank says no need to change monetary policy in coming months
-- By Teresa Cespedes 
-- Mon May 05, 2014 04:52PM EDT
-- None



LIMA, May 5 (Reuters) - Peru's central bank will likely leave monetary policy unchanged in coming months as the economy is seen growing near its potential and inflation will not be driven by demand, Central Bank President Julio Velarde told Reuters on Monday.

